1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
收集在迷失的世界中
Gathering up what's left of justice
隐藏着的细碎正义感
Hidden in this lost world
先迎面而上吧
Let's see who wins
-是长是短 -来比比看
It's not over until it's over
-珍贵的东西 -要守护好
I won't give up what's precious to me
-千元 -律师
One Dollar Lawyer

2
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,120
强大的智慧和正义的勇士
A warrior of justice with high intellect

3
00:00:02,290 --> 00:00:05,830
别担心 我是千元律师
Don't worry I'm the One Dollar Lawyer

4
00:00:07,920 --> 00:00:09,960
《平价正义》
ONE DOLLAR LAWYER

5
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:12,300
千智勋律师是个什么样的人啊
What is Mr. Cheon like?

6
00:00:12,380 --> 00:00:14,380
你就告诉我他当检察官时怎么样吧
Tell me how he was as a prosecutor.

7
00:00:14,470 --> 00:00:15,920
我们是从首尔中央地方检察厅来的
We're from Seoul Central District Prosecutors' Office.

8
00:00:16,130 --> 00:00:18,300
-你晚来了一步 -你比我想象中更果断
-You're a little too late. -You're bolder than I thought.

9
00:00:18,550 --> 00:00:20,640
现以销毁证据的嫌疑将你紧急逮捕
Mr. Choi Kitae, you're under arrest for destroying evidence.

10
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:22,890
只要我打一通电话 你们就都完了
You guys are all dead with this one phone call.

11
00:00:22,970 --> 00:00:23,810
喂 混蛋
Hey, you jerk!

12
00:00:23,890 --> 00:00:24,980
你当那是什么地方 竟敢随便去
How dare you go there?

13
00:00:25,730 --> 00:00:28,230
好好听上级的话 你才能出人头地
You'll go far if you listen to your boss.

14
00:00:28,310 --> 00:00:30,770
如果我们现在把他带回去 就和他说的一样 我们得马上放了他
We'll have to release him immediately as he said.

15
00:00:30,860 --> 00:00:32,690
我觉得你要变得有名一点 民赫
I think you should become famous, Minhyeok.

16
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:36,110
富三代和检察官一同站在红毯上
"Third Generation Chaebol and a Prosecutor Stand Together on the Red Carpet."

17
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,070
你这家伙为什么会出现在那里啊
Why would you stand there, you jerk?

18
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:39,530
你现在打算怎么办啊
What are you going to do now?

19
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:41,450
他们会请水平高超的律师
They will hire an above-average lawyer.

20
00:00:41,530 --> 00:00:42,790
告诉他们不用让着我
Tell them to come at me.

21
00:00:42,870 --> 00:00:45,500
就应该把他那样的家伙抓起来 让他赎罪 不是吗
Shouldn't a jerk like him be made to pay for his crimes?

22
00:00:45,580 --> 00:00:47,870
对 当然了 但这里是男卫生间
Yes, you're right. But this is the men's room.

23
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:49,710
喂 是白法律事务所 我们怎么办
It's Mr. Baek's firm. What do we do?

24
00:00:49,790 --> 00:00:51,920
我们又得和老头们较量一番了
I guess we have to go another round with the old men.

25
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:54,210
原来她是对方的律师啊
She was their lawyer.

26
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:56,090
李律师 你在耍我吗
Excuse me. Were you playing with me?

27
00:00:56,170 --> 00:00:57,260
我们去喝杯咖啡吧
Do you want to get some coffee?

28
00:00:57,470 --> 00:00:59,380
我刚才说的话是发自内心的
I meant… what I said earlier.

29
00:00:59,470 --> 00:01:01,970
犯了罪的人就应该受到应有的惩罚
The person who committed a crime must be punished accordingly.

30
00:01:02,050 --> 00:01:03,010
这就是我的想法
That's what I think.

31
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:05,060
你一定要赢下这场官司
Please win this trial.

32
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:07,520
我作为律师也会全力以赴
As an attorney, I'll do my best as well.

33
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:11,190
庭审中败诉的人请客喝酒怎么样 千智勋检察官
Shall we say that whoever loses has to buy the other person a drink, Mr. Cheon?

34
00:01:35,630 --> 00:01:38,510
杨尚久 JQ建设财务科长
YANG SANGGU FINANCE MANAGER OF JQ CONSTRUCTION

35
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:14,080
请你一定要遵守承诺
You have to… keep your promise.

36
00:02:36,110 --> 00:02:37,070
《第7集》
EPISODE 7

37
00:02:37,150 --> 00:02:38,530
白法律事务所
LAW FIRM BAEK

38
00:02:38,610 --> 00:02:40,150
JQ秘密资金调查案
JQ SLUSH FUND INVESTIGATION REPORT

39
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:43,110
在结束对JQ集团秘密资金的调查之前
Prior to concluding the investigation of the JQ Group slush fund,

40
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,950
检方以销毁证据为由
the prosecution arrested President Choi Kitae

41
00:02:45,030 --> 00:02:46,030
紧急逮捕了崔基泰代表
for destroying evidence.

42
00:02:46,660 --> 00:02:49,750
我们先让他免于拘留了
For now, we stopped them from arresting him.

43
00:02:49,830 --> 00:02:51,250
检方不是已经决定 以财务负责人贪污潜逃
They were supposed to close the case

44
00:02:51,330 --> 00:02:52,460
检方不是已经决定 以财务负责人贪污潜逃
saying that a finance officer embezzled the funds and disappeared.

45
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:53,830
来结束调查吗
saying that a finance officer embezzled the funds and disappeared.

46
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:58,090
是的 我们都接到了这样的通知
Yes, that's what they told us.

47
00:02:58,170 --> 00:03:00,630
那他们为什么又突然这样
Then why are they doing this now, all of a sudden?

48
00:03:02,170 --> 00:03:05,890
这个嘛 他们一定是有了新发现
They must've found something new.

49
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,390
闯祸的检察官是谁
Who's the prosecutor that caused the trouble?

50
00:03:10,020 --> 00:03:11,020
是
Yes.

51
00:03:12,890 --> 00:03:15,980
就是之前负责 扣押搜查的千智勋检察官
It's Prosecutor Cheon Jihun. He was in charge of search and seizure.

52
00:03:16,650 --> 00:03:18,980
他在高中毕业前一直住在法国巴黎
He lived in Paris, France with his mother until high school.

53
00:03:19,190 --> 00:03:22,150
和他一起生活的母亲去世后 就回到了韩国
After his mother passed away, he returned to Korea.

54
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:23,820
还真是特别
What a special case.

55
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:27,030
他和民赫是研修院同窗 所以我打听了一下
I looked into him because he trained with Minhyeok at the institute together.

56
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,660
他在韩国没有其他家人
He has no other family in Korea.

57
00:03:28,870 --> 00:03:30,870
也几乎没有同学或朋友
He has hardly any friends or schoolmates here either.

58
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:33,870
他太我行我素 连检方那边都放弃他了
He's so stubborn that even the prosecution gave up on him.

59
00:03:35,710 --> 00:03:38,420
这次高层也对此一无所知
It seems the senior officials had no idea about this either.

60
00:03:39,670 --> 00:03:43,010
所以你接下来打算如何应对
So, how do you plan to respond?

61
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:46,800
就目前的情况来看 我不知道检方手里握着什么牌
Right now, we don't know what the prosecution has.

62
00:03:47,180 --> 00:03:50,930
因此最有效的应该是 主张消失的杨尚久贪污
So it will be most effective to say Yang Sanggu has embezzled and disappeared.

63
00:03:51,350 --> 00:03:52,640
崔代表
President Choi

64
00:03:53,230 --> 00:03:56,690
想在尽可能不出席的情况下接受调查
prefers to be interviewed without attending as much as possible.

65
00:03:57,270 --> 00:04:00,230
我们能做到只让他接受书面调查吗
Can we ask for a written investigation?

66
00:04:01,230 --> 00:04:03,940
从千智勋检察官的性格来看 我想这很难
I think it would be difficult

67
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:05,740
从千智勋检察官的性格来看 我想这很难
considering Prosecutor Cheon Jihun's style.

68
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,780
你别太担心
Don't worry too much.

69
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,580
明天我打个电话
I will make a call tomorrow.

70
00:04:21,590 --> 00:04:23,880
是谁制造舆论说检方过度调查
Who drove the public opinion that the investigation is overly harsh?

71
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:28,640
犯了罪就要受到应有的惩罚 这才是正义
If one has committed a crime, they must be punished accordingly. That's justice.

72
00:04:29,220 --> 00:04:33,350
请大家帮助我们建设 一个正义尚存的韩国
Please help us to ensure justice lives in Korea.

73
00:04:39,810 --> 00:04:41,650
受到应有的惩罚…
Must be punished accordingly…

74
00:04:43,070 --> 00:04:44,150
才是正义
That's justice.

75
00:04:49,030 --> 00:04:50,370
是 前辈
Yes, Mr. Seo.

76
00:04:50,570 --> 00:04:51,830
请相信我
You can count on me.

77
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:56,080
那就说好了 崔基泰代表不用出席 只接受书面调查
Then President Choi Kitae will do a written investigation without attendance.

78
00:04:56,660 --> 00:04:57,830
我们找个时间喝一杯吧
Let's get a drink sometime. Is Minhyeok doing well?

79
00:04:58,420 --> 00:04:59,540
我家民赫表现还不错吧
Let's get a drink sometime. Is Minhyeok doing well?

80
00:05:01,130 --> 00:05:02,000
徐检察官吗
Do you mean Prosecutor Seo?

81
00:05:04,460 --> 00:05:05,550
是的
Yes.

82
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:11,850
检察

83
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:15,220
你们对崔基泰的调查 就以书面形式进行
For Choi Kitae, we will do a written investigation.

84
00:05:16,730 --> 00:05:18,890
-好的 -不行
-Yes. -We can't.

85
00:05:21,060 --> 00:05:22,020
不行？
We can't?

86
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:24,820
当初你们找不到杨尚久
If you couldn't find Yang Sanggu,

87
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,740
就不应该把事情闹大
you shouldn't have made this mess. What if he's gone off and died?

88
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:28,400
如果他死在别处了呢
you shouldn't have made this mess. What if he's gone off and died?

89
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:30,200
你要一直调查下去 直到找到他为止吗
Are you gonna investigate until you find him?

90
00:05:30,780 --> 00:05:32,990
听起来像是你盼着他死
It sounds like that's what you want.

91
00:05:33,530 --> 00:05:34,530
什么
What?

92
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:38,290
你这家伙疯了吗
Have you lost your mind?

93
00:05:38,370 --> 00:05:40,500
他写好了遗书 然后就消失了
He wrote a will and disappeared.

94
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:41,830
他肯定死在某个地方了
He must've died somewhere!

95
00:05:42,290 --> 00:05:44,840
不然你就找到他 把他带来
Then why don't you go find him and bring him in?

96
00:05:54,010 --> 00:05:56,850
次长 对不起
We're sorry, Deputy Prosecutor General.

97
00:05:56,930 --> 00:05:58,680
我们先走了 走吧
Come on, let's go.

98
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:08,530
你不好好教育后辈们 在搞什么啊
You better train your juniors better.

99
00:06:09,490 --> 00:06:11,280
好 我会的
Yes, sir. Understood.

100
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,790
首尔中央地方检察厅
SEOUL CENTRAL DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

101
00:06:20,210 --> 00:06:21,290
你被训得很惨吗
-Did you get yelled at a lot? -Yes, a lot.

102
00:06:21,370 --> 00:06:23,000
嗯 很惨
-Did you get yelled at a lot? -Yes, a lot.

103
00:06:23,380 --> 00:06:25,170
你们打算一直到处闯祸吗
Are you going to keep causing trouble?

104
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,510
对不起 但是前辈
I'm sorry. But Yejin,

105
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:31,300
我们不是到处闯祸 而是收拾残局…
we weren't causing trouble. We were trying to fix the--

106
00:06:31,380 --> 00:06:34,390
-喂 -我只是不理解
-Hey. -I just don't understand.

107
00:06:34,470 --> 00:06:36,350
所有人都知道崔基泰干了坏事
Everybody knows Choi Kitae committed a crime.

108
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:38,220
我们都知道 所以呢
We do. So what?

109
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:41,520
所以为了满足他们的贪婪 我们就要愧对良心
So is it right to starve our conscience to feed their greed?

110
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,140
-这样对吗 -不对
So is it right to starve our conscience to feed their greed?

111
00:06:42,230 --> 00:06:42,890
-这样对吗 -不对
No!

112
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:48,230
当然不对
Of course, not.

113
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,200
你要去哪
-Where are you going? -I'm going to feed my conscience.

114
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,360
让自己的良心无愧
-Where are you going? -I'm going to feed my conscience.

115
00:06:57,370 --> 00:06:58,410
等等我
Wait for me.

116
00:07:15,470 --> 00:07:17,140
这是杨尚久给你的？
Mr. Yang Sanggu gave this to you?

117
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:20,390
是的 他让我好好保管
Yes. He told me to keep it safe.

118
00:07:22,180 --> 00:07:24,690
他不会有不好的想法吧
Do you think he did something bad?

119
00:07:25,850 --> 00:07:27,520
孩子们都以为他出差了
The kids think he's on a business trip.

120
00:07:29,270 --> 00:07:32,650
千检察官 请你一定要找到我的老公
Prosecutor Cheon, please find my husband.

121
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:34,860
好 我知道了
Yes, of course.

122
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:47,670
你们回来了 怎么样了
You're back. What happened?

123
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:51,920
崔基泰的出席申请批下来了
Choi Kitae's attendance was approved.

124
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:54,470
但是只有一次
But it's only for one time.

125
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,550
没问题吗
-Is that okay? -Mm.

126
00:07:58,180 --> 00:07:59,100
一次
Once...

127
00:07:59,930 --> 00:08:01,180
就够了
is enough.

128
00:08:01,770 --> 00:08:03,980
真的吗 怎么做
Really? How?

129
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:12,030
我付给你数亿韩元的律师费 你连这个都处理不了吗
I paid you, lawyers, hundreds of millions. Why can't you take care of it?

130
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:14,740
我们已经达成协议 只让你出席这一次
We agreed to a one-time attendance today.

131
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,950
我不想再看见那个臭小子了
I don't want to see that lunatic again.

132
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:20,410
除了我们事先练过的问题 其他你一概不用回答
Don't answer questions other than the ones we practiced in advance.

133
00:08:20,490 --> 00:08:23,620
我不知道 我不记得了 我只回答这两句就行吧
"I don't know. I don't remember." Do I need to say just those two things?

134
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:27,870
如果遇到了让你为难的问题 你行使沉默权就行
And for other tricky questions, you can exercise the right to silence.

135
00:08:29,130 --> 00:08:31,500
你没有什么瞒着我吧
Do you have anything you're keeping from me?

136
00:08:33,130 --> 00:08:34,090
你不相信我吗
Don't you believe me?

137
00:08:35,130 --> 00:08:37,510
是的 我不相信你
No, I do not believe you.

138
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,180
你真的是我的律师吗
Are you sure you're my lawyer?

139
00:08:40,050 --> 00:08:41,560
正因为我是你的律师 所以才不相信你
That's why I don't believe you.

140
00:08:42,220 --> 00:08:44,600
如果连我都被你背后捅一刀
If you betray me as well, then I really won't be able to defend you.

141
00:08:44,810 --> 00:08:47,020
到时候就真的没有办法为你辩护了
If you betray me as well, then I really won't be able to defend you.

142
00:08:48,310 --> 00:08:49,810
我有什么可隐瞒的
What else is there to hide?

143
00:08:51,020 --> 00:08:52,020
我没有
There's nothing.

144
00:09:29,850 --> 00:09:32,060
我手下有两千名员工
I have 2,000 people working for me.

145
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:34,900
我怎么知道他们每个人都在做什么
How can I keep track of what each one is doing?

146
00:09:35,230 --> 00:09:36,190
你们不该抓我
It's not me.

147
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:39,360
应该去抓那个贪污公款后潜逃的家伙
Go after that jerk who embezzled the company money and disappeared.

148
00:09:39,990 --> 00:09:42,280
那样的话 你的误会也会消除
That will clear up your misunderstanding.

149
00:09:42,780 --> 00:09:45,120
那家伙叫什么来着
What was the name of that jerk?

150
00:09:45,330 --> 00:09:47,000
杨尚久科长
It's Manager Yang Sanggu.

151
00:09:47,330 --> 00:09:49,540
没错 杨科长
That's right, Manager Yang.

152
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,500
我听说他写好遗书后就消失了
I heard he disappeared after writing a will.

153
00:09:51,710 --> 00:09:52,960
那他肯定死在某个地方了
Then he must be dead somewhere.

154
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,670
请你小心说话
Please be careful what you say.

155
00:09:55,090 --> 00:09:56,090
好
Okay.

156
00:09:59,010 --> 00:10:01,010
你为什么杀了杨尚久科长
Mm, why did you kill Manager Yang?

157
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:02,470
-千检察官？-什么
-Mr. Cheon? -What?

158
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:06,560
抱歉 我说错了
I'm sorry. I misspoke.

159
00:10:06,770 --> 00:10:09,060
你为什么让杨尚久科长
Why did you tell Manager Yang Sanggu...

160
00:10:09,140 --> 00:10:10,640
去死
to die?

161
00:10:15,770 --> 00:10:16,860
天啊
Gosh.

162
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:20,030
你不是检察官 是作家啊
You aren't a prosecutor. You're a novelist.

163
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,280
小说写得不错嘛
That's some piece of fiction.

164
00:10:21,450 --> 00:10:23,030
-崔代表 -你有证据吗
-Sir. -Do you have proof?

165
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:29,000
那你见过杨尚久科长吧
Then have you met Manager Yang Sanggu?

166
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,620
你不必回答
You don't have to answer that.

167
00:10:31,580 --> 00:10:34,080
这个嘛 杨科长…
Let's see, have I ever met…

168
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:36,710
我见过他吗
Manager Yang?

169
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:45,760
我应该很久没见过他了
I believe it's been quite a while since I saw him.

170
00:10:46,010 --> 00:10:47,810
自从他潜逃后 我就没再见过他
I haven't seen him since he disappeared.

171
00:10:47,890 --> 00:10:50,180
这样啊 你和他通过电话吗
I see. What about talking to him on the phone?

172
00:10:50,980 --> 00:10:51,940
电话？
On the phone?

173
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:54,520
对 在杨尚久科长死前
Yes. Before Manager Yang Sanggu died.

174
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,230
你们通过最后一次电话
You talked to him last.

175
00:10:56,770 --> 00:10:57,770
那个啊
Oh, that.

176
00:10:58,820 --> 00:11:00,820
他打电话过来道歉
He had called to say he was sorry.

177
00:11:01,070 --> 00:11:03,150
毕竟他私吞了数百亿韩元的公款
He stole tens of billions from the company.

178
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:05,910
所以我让他自首
I told him to turn himself in.

179
00:11:05,990 --> 00:11:07,990
钱重要吗 人才是最重要的
A person's life is more important than money.

180
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:09,410
不是吗 千检察官
Isn't that right, Prosecutor?

181
00:11:09,490 --> 00:11:12,750
所以你就给了杨尚久的老婆…
I guess that's why you gave his wife…

182
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:16,380
五亿韩元啊 你看看这个
five hundred million won. Take a look at this.

183
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:26,930
你想啊 我手底下的员工死了
I mean, one of my employees died.

184
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:28,890
我怎么能立刻翻脸不认人
I can't just pretend I don't know about it.

185
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:33,020
即使他贪污了数百亿韩元？
Even though he embezzled tens of billion won?

186
00:11:33,350 --> 00:11:36,770
贪污归贪污 我不是那么无情的人
Embezzlement is embezzlement. But I'm not a heartless person.

187
00:11:37,610 --> 00:11:39,610
他的家人得继续生活啊
His family has to live on.

188
00:11:41,780 --> 00:11:43,190
我给的太少了吗
Maybe I gave too little.

189
00:11:47,530 --> 00:11:50,120
智勋这家伙在想什么
What is Jihun thinking?

190
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,330
不过
But…

191
00:11:53,410 --> 00:11:55,250
打电话也有罪吗
was it a crime to talk to him on the phone?

192
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:03,970
打电话没罪 不过…
Talking to him on the phone is not a crime, but…

193
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:14,810
你让他要么跳楼 要么上吊
it could be a crime to tell him

194
00:12:14,890 --> 00:12:17,520
让他随便选 这可能有罪
to either fall off the building or hang himself.

195
00:12:23,030 --> 00:12:27,450
崔代表 我会承认是我干的 不管几年 我会去坐牢
Mr. Choi, I will tell him that I did it and go to jail for however many years.

196
00:12:27,530 --> 00:12:30,070
崔代表 我会承担所有责任
Mr. Choi, I will take all of the blame.

197
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:32,370
所以求你了
So, please…

198
00:12:33,660 --> 00:12:35,870
-你会承担所有责任？-对
-You'll take all of the blame? -Yes.

199
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,460
好 就这么办吧
Fine. Let's do that.

200
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:47,300
我会好好照顾你的家人
I will take good care of your family.

201
00:12:47,380 --> 00:12:49,890
谢谢你 崔代表
Thank you. Thank you, Mr. Choi.

202
00:12:49,970 --> 00:12:51,640
你不用谢我
You don't have to be that grateful.

203
00:12:52,470 --> 00:12:54,180
应该是我感谢你才对
I'm the one who should be grateful.

204
00:12:55,310 --> 00:12:57,980
你不是说要承担所有责任嘛
You said you will take all of the blame with you.

205
00:12:58,060 --> 00:12:59,480
是的 那么…
Yes, then…

206
00:13:00,650 --> 00:13:01,900
你要么跳楼
You can fall off a building…

207
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:04,980
要么上吊
or hang yourself.

208
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:07,360
你随便选吧
Do as you please.

209
00:13:12,990 --> 00:13:14,160
你看
See?

210
00:13:15,660 --> 00:13:16,960
我有证据
I do have evidence.

211
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:22,880
千检察官
Mr. Cheon.

212
00:13:26,510 --> 00:13:27,880
我们休息一会儿再继续吧
Let's take a short break.

213
00:13:44,690 --> 00:13:46,030
他刚才说的话是什么意思
What is he talking about?

214
00:13:48,490 --> 00:13:50,280
我得了解清楚才能制定对策
I need to know so I can plan a response.

215
00:13:50,610 --> 00:13:51,660
我让他去死
I told him to kill himself.

216
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:53,620
什么
What?

217
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,660
我让杨尚久去死
I told Yang Sanggu to kill himself. I thought that would cover it up.

218
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,250
我想那样就能掩盖这起案件
I told Yang Sanggu to kill himself. I thought that would cover it up.

219
00:13:57,500 --> 00:13:58,750
你怎么现在才告诉我
-Why are you telling me this now? -I thought you didn't believe me anyway.

220
00:13:58,830 --> 00:14:00,920
反正你又不相信我
-Why are you telling me this now? -I thought you didn't believe me anyway.

221
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:03,960
那家伙肯定是在什么地方听到的
He must've heard it somewhere.

222
00:14:04,290 --> 00:14:05,460
他没有证据
He has no proof.

223
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:09,380
杨科长 你现在这么说 但如果你在庭审中承认是我指使的
Mr. Yang, you say this now, but you may confess that I gave the order.

224
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:12,390
我的面子要往哪里搁啊
What would that do to my image?

225
00:14:13,180 --> 00:14:15,970
你不是说要承担所有责任嘛
You said you will take all of the blame with you.

226
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:17,520
是的 那么…
Yes, then…

227
00:14:18,850 --> 00:14:19,980
-你要么跳楼 -这是什么
-You can fall off a building... -What is this?

228
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:22,230
要么上吊
...or hang yourself.

229
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:24,230
你随便选吧
Do as you please.

230
00:14:27,150 --> 00:14:28,190
那家伙…
That bastard…

231
00:14:29,530 --> 00:14:31,030
是怎么拿到这个的
How did he get this?

232
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,700
李律师 我会怎么样
Ms. Lee, what's going to happen to me?

233
00:14:35,580 --> 00:14:37,370
会涉嫌教唆自杀吗
Is it something like abetting suicide?

234
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,830
-不会 -不会吗
-No. -It's not?

235
00:14:40,290 --> 00:14:41,250
也是
That makes sense.

236
00:14:41,330 --> 00:14:44,000
让他去死 他就去死的人才是傻瓜 不是吗
It's stupid to kill yourself just because someone tells you to, right?

237
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,960
如果这段录音属实
If this recording is true,

238
00:14:47,050 --> 00:14:51,420
根据《刑法》第253条 这将构成胁迫他人自杀罪
it will be a crime of suicide by force in Article 253 of the Criminal Law.

239
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:55,640
胁迫…什么 很严重吗
Suicide by force… What is it? Is it bad?

240
00:14:56,010 --> 00:14:58,810
不 不是很严重
No, it's not that bad.

241
00:14:58,890 --> 00:14:59,890
那就好
That's good.

242
00:14:59,970 --> 00:15:03,900
就只会受到和杀人罪差不多的惩罚
The punishment will be similar to that of murder.

243
00:15:05,270 --> 00:15:07,070
杀人罪？
Murder?

244
00:15:09,650 --> 00:15:10,690
你在开玩笑吗
Are you kidding me?

245
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,860
人又不是我杀的 这太荒唐了
That doesn't make sense. I didn't kill him.

246
00:15:15,490 --> 00:15:16,740
你没有办法吗
Is there no other way?

247
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:19,660
你说啊
Is there?

248
00:15:20,410 --> 00:15:21,500
李律师
Ms. Lee!

249
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:37,800
杨尚久？
Mr. Yang Sanggu?

250
00:15:40,010 --> 00:15:41,100
杨尚久
Mr. Yang Sanggu.

251
00:15:44,310 --> 00:15:45,520
你怎么…
How did you…

252
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:51,940
千检察官 你是怎么找到我的
Mr. Cheon, how did you find me?

253
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:59,950
杨尚久 你认为这样做 就能解决所有问题吗
Mr. Yang Sanggu, did you think you could solve everything by doing this?

254
00:16:01,370 --> 00:16:02,700
并不是
It wasn't that,

255
00:16:03,540 --> 00:16:05,670
但如果我活着回去 他会杀了我
but if I go back alive, he will kill me.

256
00:16:06,330 --> 00:16:07,380
是谁
Who will?

257
00:16:07,630 --> 00:16:08,920
崔基泰代表
President Choi Kitae.

258
00:16:11,170 --> 00:16:13,340
他完全有可能这么做
He is capable of doing that and more.

259
00:16:14,340 --> 00:16:15,590
不会的
That's probably not true.

260
00:16:17,180 --> 00:16:18,140
什么
What?

261
00:16:19,260 --> 00:16:22,220
他见到你 反而会比任何人都高兴
He will actually be happy to see you, more than anyone.

262
00:16:24,270 --> 00:16:25,350
他见到我会高兴？
He will be happy to see me?

263
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:27,900
对 我可以向你保证
Yes. I can promise you that.

264
00:16:31,190 --> 00:16:32,690
杨尚久 这由你来决定
It's your decision, Mr. Yang.

265
00:16:34,190 --> 00:16:37,240
是就这么死在这里
You can die here like this,

266
00:16:37,570 --> 00:16:40,780
还是回去和崔基泰一起接受惩罚
or return and pay the price with Choi Kitae.

267
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:45,370
这完全是你的选择
The choice is solely yours.

268
00:16:59,430 --> 00:17:03,010
既然你见到他了 就应该想尽办法劝他回来
I mean, you should've talked him into coming back.

269
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,140
你怎么就这么回来了
Why didn't you?

270
00:17:04,220 --> 00:17:06,930
你不是检察官 简直是个疯子
He's not a prosecutor. He's a crazy bastard!

271
00:17:07,350 --> 00:17:09,600
你之前不是还让他去死吗
You told him to kill himself.

272
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,900
如果你想让他回来 那就祈祷吧
You should pray if you want Mr. Yang Sanggu to come back.

273
00:17:13,820 --> 00:17:15,320
你这是要干什么
What are you trying to do?

274
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:16,860
如果他不回来的话会怎么样
What happens if he doesn't come back?

275
00:17:18,950 --> 00:17:19,950
说话啊
Tell me!

276
00:17:22,490 --> 00:17:23,910
崔基泰
Mr. Choi Kitae.

277
00:17:24,620 --> 00:17:28,000
我们以胁迫他人自杀的嫌疑 将你紧急逮捕
I arrest you for the charge of suicide of Yang Sanggu by force.

278
00:17:28,710 --> 00:17:31,290
你有权保持沉默 也有权请律师…
You have the right to remain silent, you have the right to a lawyer…

279
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:38,550
你应该不用请律师了 你已经有了
I guess you don't have to hire a lawyer since you have one already.

280
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:41,340
-把他带走 -是
-Take him away. -Yes, sir.

281
00:17:44,180 --> 00:17:46,560
李律师 你想办法救救我
Ms. Lee, do something.

282
00:17:47,230 --> 00:17:48,430
我没杀他啊
I didn't kill him.

283
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:51,100
你现在说的话 可能会在庭审中对你不利
Whatever you say now can work against you at trial.

284
00:17:56,530 --> 00:18:00,700
检察

285
00:18:09,330 --> 00:18:10,500
杨科长
Mr. Yang.

286
00:18:12,790 --> 00:18:14,380
你还活着啊
You were alive.

287
00:18:16,050 --> 00:18:17,880
你怎么现在才来
What took you so long?

288
00:18:18,670 --> 00:18:21,510
来得好 你来得真是太及时了
I'm glad you came back. I'm really glad.

289
00:18:21,590 --> 00:18:23,590
你救了我一命
You saved me, Mr. Yang.

290
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:26,220
那我不会被指控杀人了吧
Does this mean I'm not charged with murder?

291
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:31,190
你来得好
I'm so glad you're back!

292
00:18:33,230 --> 00:18:35,860
-你没事吧 -是的
-Are you okay? -Yes.

293
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:42,910
你来得好
I'm glad you're here.

294
00:18:44,820 --> 00:18:46,410
但如果我活着回去
If I go back alive,

295
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:48,540
他会杀了我
he will kill me.

296
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,120
不会的
That's probably not true.

297
00:18:50,910 --> 00:18:51,910
什么
What?

298
00:18:55,330 --> 00:18:58,800
他见到你 反而会比任何人都高兴
He will actually be happy to see you more than anyone.

299
00:18:59,170 --> 00:19:00,380
他见到我会高兴？
He will be happy to see me?

300
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:02,800
对 我可以向你保证
Yes, I can promise you that.

301
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:06,760
杨尚久
Mr. Yang Sanggu.

302
00:19:06,970 --> 00:19:10,060
解决问题的方式有很多种
There are many ways to solve a problem.

303
00:19:11,060 --> 00:19:13,480
因为陷入了最绝望的时刻
When you are in the most desperate situation,

304
00:19:14,980 --> 00:19:17,110
你就放弃你承受不了的那条活路
is it the best choice

305
00:19:18,020 --> 00:19:20,440
这是最好的选择吗
to just give up on everything that you can't handle?

306
00:19:37,790 --> 00:19:39,750
杨尚久回来了
Yang Sanggu has returned.

307
00:19:41,130 --> 00:19:45,340
《平价正义》
ONE DOLLAR LAWYER

308
00:19:45,430 --> 00:19:48,430
首尔中央地方法院
SEOUL CENTRAL DISTRICT COURT

309
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:55,560
-来了 -他来了
-There he is. -There he comes.

310
00:19:57,730 --> 00:20:00,190
-你承认所有指控吗 -你现在心情如何
-Do you admit to everything? -What are your thoughts?

311
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:02,610
请你说句话 大家都想知道
Everyone wants to know. Please say something.

312
00:20:02,690 --> 00:20:04,950
-你对判决怎么看 -请你说句话
-What do you think of the verdict? -Do you have anything to say?

313
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:07,490
请你说句话
Can you give a statement?

314
00:20:07,570 --> 00:20:09,990
-你承认指控吗 -你承认吗
-Do you admit to the charges? -Do you agree?

315
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:12,540
是的 我承认所有指控
Yes. I admit to all of the charges.

316
00:20:12,830 --> 00:20:15,410
但至少我没有杀人
It's not like I killed a man.

317
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:17,710
-这是什么意思 -这话是什么意思
-What does that mean? -What do you mean?

318
00:20:17,790 --> 00:20:20,540
-崔基泰 -你再说几句吧
-Mr. Choi Kitae! -Can you comment on that?

319
00:20:20,630 --> 00:20:22,880
-崔基泰 -请再说几句
-Mr. Choi Kitae! -Any other comments?

320
00:20:39,860 --> 00:20:40,860
就是这里吗
Is this the place?

321
00:20:41,650 --> 00:20:45,110
我说过会请你喝酒 可没说会请你喝很贵的酒
I told you I would buy you a drink. I never said it would be expensive.

322
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:47,450
那样会违反《禁止不正当请托法》
I don't want to violate the Improper Solicitation Act.

323
00:20:47,530 --> 00:20:51,120
我说要打赌请客喝酒 可没说要和你一起喝
I said I would wager a drink. I didn't say I would drink with you.

324
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,330
你要这么不讲情面吗
So you will be difficult.

325
00:20:56,540 --> 00:20:59,540
不过严格来说 我没有输
Technically speaking, I didn't lose.

326
00:20:59,630 --> 00:21:01,460
因为在那天之后 他换了律师
He changed his lawyer after that day.

327
00:21:03,090 --> 00:21:05,340
所以你认为如果你继续为他辩护
Do you think the outcome would've been different

328
00:21:05,420 --> 00:21:08,090
结果会有所不同吗
if you had stayed on as his lawyer?

329
00:21:09,180 --> 00:21:10,010
这个嘛
Hmm. I'm not sure.

330
00:21:12,430 --> 00:21:13,470
不会
No.

331
00:21:15,020 --> 00:21:17,890
阿姨 我们要生啤酒和一盘明太鱼干
Ma'am, can we have draft beers and a plate of dried pollack?

332
00:21:17,980 --> 00:21:19,060
好的
Sure.

333
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:23,520
你在干什么 至少应该让我来点下酒菜吧
What are you doing? Shouldn't I at least choose the food?

334
00:21:24,820 --> 00:21:26,530
你不喜欢明太鱼干吗
Don't you like dried pollack?

335
00:21:28,860 --> 00:21:30,820
我不是不喜欢…
It's not that I don't like dried pollack…

336
00:21:31,910 --> 00:21:35,200
你没吃过吧 就像你没喝过自动贩卖机里的咖啡
You've never had it, just like coffee from a vending machine.

337
00:21:38,210 --> 00:21:39,420
怎么会这样
How can that be?

338
00:21:40,080 --> 00:21:42,840
你该不会挑食吧
Is it because you're a picky eater?

339
00:21:44,050 --> 00:21:45,630
我吃过明太鱼干
I've had dried pollack before.

340
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:02,310
吃明太鱼干吧
Have some dried pollack.

341
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,870
不过千检察官
So, Mr. Cheon.

342
00:22:21,250 --> 00:22:24,590
如果杨尚久真的不回来 你打算怎么办
What were you going to do if Mr. Yang Sanggu never came back?

343
00:22:25,670 --> 00:22:27,050
就这么任由他自杀吗
Would you have left him to die?

344
00:22:30,050 --> 00:22:32,260
对任何人来说 做选择都很困难 不是吗
Making a choice is hard for anyone.

345
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:37,640
不管再怎么困难
No matter how hard it is,

346
00:22:38,350 --> 00:22:39,980
别人都不能替你做出选择
-others can't make the choice for you. -Aah.

347
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:42,690
你真的是检察官吗
Are you sure you're a prosecutor?

348
00:22:44,360 --> 00:22:46,570
对 没错 你真的是律师吗
Yes, I'm sure. Are you sure you're a lawyer?

